  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trader",
  "description": "<p>Astignes Capital is an\nAsia-focused alternative investment management firm based in Singapore. We\nlaunched our flagship Asia Rates fund in 2007, and our investment strategy aims\nto capture macro and relative value opportunities in the Asia-Pacific region\nprimarily through the use of interest rates, FX and volatility instruments.</p><p>The firm is seeking an Asia\nRates and/or FX trader to join the firm’s investment\nteam. As a member of Astignes Capital’s investment\nteam, you will help manage the firm’s investment\nprocess, including using quantitative approaches to generate trading ideas,\nimplementing various investment strategies, and managing and monitoring the\nportfolio’s risk and positioning.</p><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>5 years of experience in trading Rates and/or FX instruments – ideally at top-tier buyside macro firms</li><li>A strong, demonstrated multi-year performance track record executing directional or relative value trading strategies in Asia</li><li>A degree in Finance, Mathematics, or a similar quantitative field from a globally recognized university</li></ul>",
